{"key":"processedPost-12427979","value":{"id":12427979,"first":12427635,"last":12428237,"when":1271809011,"utime":"04/21/10 03:16 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Stillmatic9142 said:</b><br />Should the frosting layer be mixed in with the top of substrate or just sprinkled lightly on top?<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Neither.&nbsp; The idea of 'frosting' is bad practice.&nbsp; Don't have any exposed grains on the surface.&nbsp; Doing so leads to a higher incidence of contamination because the grains dry out, which weakens the mushroom mycelium, allowing molds like trichoderma to enter the exposed grains.&nbsp; Make sure you always have a layer of substrate or casing material over any grains.<br />RR","title":"Re: Frosting Layer","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}